  "body": "After spinning up a fresh GCE cluster, I found that when SSHing into individual instances that kubectl does not exist. I tried following the documentation for setting up kubectl using gcloud, but the gcloud that is already installed on the instances is out of date and conflicts with the documentation. \n\nIs there any way to update the GKE images to include the latest gcloud with kubectl already installed and authorized (via service accounts) to access the kubernetes API? Otherwise, I am having to manually authorize kubectl via service accounts / web tokens and am doing this manually for each instance.\n",
